J(x, y, z) = x^a + y^b + z^c
J
 x + y + z = D
H(x,y,z,\lambda):=x^a+y^b+z^c-\lambda(x+y+z-D)
H_x'=H_y'=H_z'=H_\lambda'=0\;\;\ldots
C(x,y,z) = x+y+z-D=0
L(x,y,z,\lambda) := J(x,y,z) = J(x,y,z)-\lambda \cdot C(x,y,z)
\nabla L=0
\frac{\partial L}{\partial x}=0 \\  \frac{\partial L}{\partial y}=0 \\ \frac{\partial L}{\partial z}=0 \\ 
 \frac{\partial L}{\partial \lambda}=C(x,y,z)=0 \\ 
